From behnke 'Broomen' Behnke Subject Re Electric power line balls In article Scott Townsend writes I got a question from my dad which I really can't answer and I'd appreciate some His question is about some diameter balls which are attached to electric power lines in his He's seen up to a half dozen between two Neither of us have any experience with electric power My only guess was that they may be a capacitive device to equalize the inductance of the grid but why so many between two poles Anyone know what they really are Is there a related FAQ for this Is there a better group to submit to We'd both appreciate some The balls are used to reduce the amplitude of oscillations of the wire during periods of high I've seen what looks like paint cans filled with concrete used for the same Mike Behnke Senior Tech Advisor Quid est illuidin aqua Fermi Nat Accel Lab Equipment Suuport Batavia Computing Div PISTRIX PISTRIX BEHNKE My opinions are my own not of the So if you don't like them call UWH INER